43.task: Touch exactly one object that is [partially but not all] blue.

STUDENT.observations: It was quite tedious, but got easier over time. Took forever at first because he kept failing me. You could specify that the student can also move during teaching rounds? (Unless I just missed that part in the instructions...). Not sure if that actually helps with communication because it didn't for me, but maybe for others.
STUDENT.guess: Touch the objects that don't have all their halves visible

TEACHER.observations: This was fun but very challenging in some cases. I guess I have to make some actions that both myself and the student can agree. But since the move is very slow and hard to control, it was hard to make one. Also, some actions that I tried to make was understood incorrectly but the student so I ended up not using since it would be confusing for the student. For example, I drew a small circle to illustrate a small object but the student was thinking that the movement itself was the task so he/she copied the circling movement.
